<Author>travelalot2
<Content>in the middle of beautiful nature We have chosen this place primarily due to architecture and setting promissed on the FS website. And we did not regret the choice at all. Design of this hotel is truly unique. Especially impressive were beautifully landscaped grounds rolling down to the Ayung river. Similarly impressive was the entrance including the lobby which was already being described in others reviews. And here our wow is about to end. In terms of rooms we were quite surprised that the suite was already little run down, but still good sized and giving comfortable ambiance. Big windows over both floors giving the vue of rice fields behind were amazing. So that without this view, being this hotel in other place I would probably never pay for this room such a premium.The restaurant located in -2 floor of the main building again takes all its advantage from the river gorge view. Otherwise is rather overpriced and we used it only for breakfast which was included in our rate. And here I want to mention a rather weird and for us unacceptable experience. Though included in price we have been always given the bill at the end to sign (to be deducted at check out) giving the impression that they want to show us how much they spent on us, like giving us the breakfast free. Yes it was by the prices there always above 100USD bill for simple breakfast for 2. But if they offer a BB rate they just should let you have a breakfast and go like in other places. This made us feel sorry for them and give them lot of points on our impression scale down.In terms of dinner the main attraction for us - view - has faded away in dark so we rather took the shuttle bus to Ubud and enjoyed good food and wines in town. We found Ary鈥檚 Warung being the best, though strangely not being on the concierge list in the hotel. Probably too big competition for the hotels restaurant.And last but not least - the so much praised in other reviews - service. Definitely the staff is perfectly trained to show the guests that they do everything to make them feel welcome and meet your every need. But honestly this comes somehow too much and unbelievable. If you are asked during your teatime four times by three different people if your tea is good and if they can do something for us is honestly almost annoying. And if the smile from the person disappears seconds after its steps from you, hey, believe it is coming from heart. We did not. But besides this feeling the service was prompt and generally nice. But do not forget you are in Bali and the service is amazing almost everywhere.In summary I dont want to give feeling it is bad hotel. It is truly 5*experience with amazing facilities and setting. But when we were leaving we missed this special feeling that we are sorry to leave and we want to return soon. 
