<Author>fabholslover
<Content>Oh my!!! We have just returned from our third trip to Bali - last year we spent our usual time at the coast but wanted to then spend a couple of days up in the Ubud area. I chose what I thought would be a 'nice' hotel but were very let down by the standard etc  felt our holiday had been compromised. This year we decided to leave nothing to chance  stay at the Four Seasons Sayan - all I can say is 'wow' what a hotel!People seem to be divided on this site as to whether they love or hate the design of this hotel - we were extremely impressed with the way the modern design blends so well with the natural environment - its absolutely beautiful. One thing that did surprise me is how small the overall property is - its easy to walk around (provided you can manage the steps as it is built on a hillside) so we never called for a buggy - just enjoyed the grounds.We stayed in a villa and it was very peaceful with lovely views across the rice fields and amazingly private. The villa itself was spacious and had every amenity you could want. My husband  I were travelling with our 13 year old daughter and there was plenty of room for an extra bed etc without feeling cramped. (She especially liked the plunge pool!)We had breakfast at the main restaurant, lunch at the pool and two evening meals in the restaurant. The views from the restaurant are incredible (as all the photos on this site show). Once again I notice that people are divided as to the standard of food - all I can say is that we found it to be superb and as to the price - well, folks in this life you get what you pay for! Everything was of the highest quality but what really did stand out for us was the service. We had a slight problem with one dessert order and they went above and beyond in dealing with it even to the extent of offering us a complementary dessert the following day. Everyone from the General Manager down greeted us with a smile and looked after our every comfort without being intrusive.We absolutely loved this hotel  would return in a heart beat. 
