<Content>Nice The bottom line with this Hotel is that it is perfect in terms of service and design. We spent four days here for our honeymoon after four days at the Oberoi in Seminyak. We were upgraded to a river villa close to the main hotel. It was a beautiful room with a plunge pool looking over the gorge. The hotel hits all of those Four Seasons requirements for service and style. We loved the Yoga, guided bike ride and the guided trek through the local area. The town of Ubud is full of fun things to do and food to eat. The only complaint i really have is the food. Bali has wonderful food but the Four Seasons really dumbs things down to make the world traveller comfortable about being away from home. I found the restaurants to be souless if that makes sense. We left every night to eat in Ubud after our first dinner at the hotel. That would be my only complaint. The setting is spectacular and the people nice. It was very very quiet however. For the price I would probably not return however. The Oberoi (see my review) in Seminyak is literally 1/3 of the cost yet is very comparable. No regrets, but I would probably do something different if I was to return to Ubud (maybe the Maya or the Como Shambala resort). 
